Lead.text: 2016-07-07 00:50fileIn the east, Daenerys Targaryen, the last scion of House Targaryen, rules with her three dragons as queen of a city built on dust and death.
2016-07-07 00:50fileBut Daenerys has thousands of enemies, and many have set out to find her.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Fleeing from Westeros with a price on his head, Tyrion Lannister, too, is making his way to Daenerys.
2016-07-07 00:50fileThere, Jon Snow, 998th Lord Commander of the NightвЂ™s Watch, will face his greatest challenge.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > for Lodey, Trebla, Stego, Pod, < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Bronn Stone, CoyoteвЂ™s Daughter, < / p >

2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > Whereas < emphasis > Feast < / emphasis > focused on events in and around KingвЂ™s Landing, on the Iron Islands, and down in Dorne, < emphasis > Dance < / emphasis > takes us north to Castle Black and the Wall (and beyond), and across the narrow sea to Pentos and SlaverвЂ™s Bay, to pick up the tales of Tyrion Lannister, Jon Snow, Daenerys Targaryen, and all the other characters you did
2016-07-07 00:50fileOthers were slain by those who had been their brothers-in-arms when they marched south with Mance Rayder, the King-Beyond-the-Wall.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > < emphasis > Mance is fallen, < / emphasis > the survivors told each other in despairing voices, < emphasis > Mance is taken, Mance is dead.

2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > вЂњHarmaвЂ™s dead and Mance is captured, the rest run off and left us, вЂќ Thistle had claimed, as she was sewing up his wound. вЂњTormund, the Weeper, Sixskins, all them brave raiders.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > I was Varamyr Six-skins, who broke bread with Mance Rayder.

2016-07-07 00:50fileHis sleeping pelts and woolen smallclothes, his sheepskin boots and fur-lined gloves, his store of mead and hoarded food, the hanks of hair he took from the women he bedded, even the golden arm rings Mance had given him, all lost and left behind.
2016-07-07 00:50fileIf Mance is dead, the free folk are doomed.
2016-07-07 00:50fileHe rode to battle on the back of a snow bear thirteen feet tall, kept three wolves and a shadowcat in thrall, and sat at the right hand of Mance Rayder.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > It was Mance who brought me to this place.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Before Mance, Varamyr Sixskins had been a lord of sorts.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > Snow.
2016-07-07 00:50fileMance would have cursed him as well, but Mance was slain or captured.

2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > It would be good to feel warm again, though it made him sad to think that he would never see the green lands, the warm lands beyond the Wall that Mance used to sing about. вЂњThe world beyond the Wall is not for our kind, вЂќ Haggon used to say. вЂњThe free folk fear skinchangers, but they honor us as well.
2016-07-07 00:50fileOrell had been slain by the turncloak crow Jon Snow, and his hate for his killer had been so strong that Varamyr found himself hating the beastling boy as well.
2016-07-07 00:50fileHe had known what Snow was the moment he saw that great white direwolf stalking silent at his side.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > Mance should have let me take the direwolf.
2016-07-07 00:50fileThe gift was strong in Snow, but the youth was untaught, still fighting his nature when he should have gloried in it.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > TYRION < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion marked time by the comings and goings of the cabin boy who brought the meals he did not eat.

2016-07-07 00:50fileThe boy always brought a brush and bucket too, to clean up. вЂњIs this Dornish wine? вЂќ Tyrion asked him once, as he pulled a stopper from a skin. вЂњIt reminds me of a certain snake I knew.

2016-07-07 00:50fileHe was an ugly boy, though admittedly more comely than a certain dwarf with half a nose and a scar from eye to chin. вЂњHave I offended you? вЂќ Tyrion asked, as the boy was scrubbing. вЂњWere you commanded not to talk to me?
2016-07-07 00:50fileTell me that.вЂќ Jaime had made mention of the Free Cities, but had never said which one. вЂњIs it Braavos?
2016-07-07 00:50fileMyr? вЂќ Tyrion would sooner have gone to Dorne.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > Myrcella is older than Tommen, by Dornish law the Iron Throne is hers.
2016-07-07 00:50fileI will help her claim her rights, as Prince Oberyn suggested.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Oberyn was dead, though, his head smashed to bloody ruin by the armored fist of Ser Gregor Clegane.
2016-07-07 00:50fileAnd without the Red Viper to urge him on, would Doran Martell even consider such a chancy scheme?
2016-07-07 00:50fileOld Bear Mormont said the NightвЂ™s Watch had need of men like Tyrion.
2016-07-07 00:50fileJanos Slynt would see to that.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > The cabin boy wet his brush and scrubbed on manfully. вЂњHave you ever visited the pleasure houses of Lys? вЂќ the dwarf inquired. вЂњMight that be where whores go? вЂќ Tyrion could not seem to recall the Valyrian word for whore, and in any case it was too late.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion had some Braavosi and a smattering of Myrish.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Sleep had never come easily to Tyrion Lannister.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > It was all beyond his reach, Tyrion knew now.

2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > The crossbow < emphasis > thrumm < / emphasis > ed, Lord Tywin sat back down, and Tyrion Lannister found himself waddling through the darkness with Varys at his side.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Varys had escorted him through the tunnels, but they never spoke until they emerged beside the Blackwater, where Tyrion had won a famous victory and lost a nose.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњWherever whores go.вЂќ Tyrion had warned his father not to say that word.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњI killed Shae too, вЂќ he confessed to Varys.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Varys tittered. вЂњAnd now you do.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50fileVarys had saved him from a headsmanвЂ™s sword, but only because Jaime had compelled him.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > Jaime вЂ ¦ no, better not to think of Jaime.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion told him to be quiet and kicked feebly as a huge bald sailor tucked him under one arm and carried him squirming to the hold, where an empty wine cask awaited him.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion pissed himself in his struggles, for all the good it did.
2016-07-07 00:50fileAnother cask slammed into his, and Tyrion bit his tongue.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion gasped greedily and tried to stand, but only managed to knock the cask over sideways and spill himself out onto a hard-packed earthen floor.
2016-07-07 00:50fileHe reminded Tyrion of a dead sea cow that had once washed up in the caverns under Casterly Rock.
2016-07-07 00:50fileI like that in a dwarf.вЂќ When the fat man laughed, his flesh bounced so vigorously that Tyrion was afraid he might fall and crush him. вЂњAre you hungry, my little friend?
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњThirsty.вЂќ Tyrion struggled to his knees. вЂњAnd filthy.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50fileAny friend of my friend across the water is a friend to Illyrio Mopatis, yes.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > < emphasis > And any friend of Varys the Spider is someone I will trust just as far as I can throw him.
2016-07-07 00:50fileNo sooner did Tyrion lower himself into the hot water and close his eyes than he was fast asleep.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion shook the last drops off and waddled over patterned Myrish carpets as soft as new spring grass.
2016-07-07 00:50fileAwkwardly he climbed the window seat and flung the shutters open to see where Varys and the gods had sent him.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > When he heard the door opening behind him, Tyrion turned to confront his fat host. вЂњThis is Pentos, yes? вЂќ < / p >

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > The fat man stroked one of the prongs of his oiled yellow beard, a gesture Tyrion found remarkably obscene. вЂњSlavery is forbidden in Pentos, by the terms of the treaty the Braavosi imposed on us a hundred years ago.
2016-07-07 00:50fileStill, they will not refuse you.вЂќ Illyrio gave a ponderous half bow. вЂњBut now my little friend must excuse me.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњYes, my fat friend, вЂќ Tyrion replied.
2016-07-07 00:50fileShould a day ever dawn when Illyrio Mopatis saw more profit in a dead dwarf than a live one, Tyrion would find himself packed into another wine cask by dusk.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > That it would arrive he did not doubt; Cersei was not like to forget him, and even Jaime might be vexed to find a quarrel in FatherвЂ™s belly.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњWherever whores go, вЂќ he heard Lord Tywin say once more, and once more the bowstring < emphasis > thrum < / emphasis > med.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Tyrion began his explorations with the kitchen, where two fat women and a potboy watched him warily as he helped himself to cheese, bread, and figs. вЂњGood morrow to you, fair ladies, вЂќ he said with a bow. вЂњDo you know where whores go? вЂќ When they did not respond, he repeated the question in High Valyrian, though he had to say < emphasis > courtesan < / emphasis > in place of < emphasis
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > None will dare refuse you, < / emphasis > Illyrio claimed, but somehow Tyrion did not think he meant these two.
2016-07-07 00:50fileBoth were near as fat as Illyrio, with teats that were larger than his head.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > Lord Tywin might have been niggardly with his approval and affection, but he had always been open-handed when it came to coin.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Tyrion left the fat women to their loaves and kettles and went in search of the cellar where Illyrio had decanted him the night before.
2016-07-07 00:50fileIn the end, Tyrion chose a cask of strongwine marked as the private stock of Lord Runceford Redwyne, the grandfather of the present Lord of the Arbor.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion filled a cup, and a flagon for good measure, and carried them up to the gardens to drink beneath those cherry trees heвЂ™d seen.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion pictured how his sisterвЂ™s head might look up there, with tar in her golden hair and flies buzzing in and out of her mouth.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > Yes, and Jaime must have the spike beside her, < / emphasis > he decided.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion knew eunuchs when he saw them.

2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion settled on a stone bench with his flagon. вЂњTell me, how far should I trust Magister Illyrio? вЂќ The name made her look up. вЂњThat far? вЂќ Chuckling, he crossed his stunted legs and took a drink. вЂњI am loath to play whatever part the cheesemonger has in mind for me, yet how can I refuse him?
2016-07-07 00:50fileI could make rather a lot of mischief in Dorne with Myrcella.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > I cannot seem to hold a wife for very long, < / emphasis > Tyrion reflected.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > Or better yet, he should have asked his father. вЂњWherever whores go, вЂќ Lord Tywin said.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion pushed himself off the bench and went to fetch it.
2016-07-07 00:50fileMagister Illyrio expects you at table within the hour.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Tyrion propped himself against the pillows, his head in his hands. вЂњDo I dream, or do you speak the Common Tongue? вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > She poured for him. вЂњMagister Illyrio said that I am to scrub your back and warm your bed.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > That he had fucked many a woman who loathed the very sight of him, Tyrion Lannister had no doubt, but the others had at least the grace to feign affection.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > Even Lord Tywin had not been afraid, though Tyrion had held a crossbow in his hands. вЂњDo you moan when you are being fucked? вЂќ he asked the bedwarmer.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Illyrio was reclining on a padded couch, gobbling hot peppers and pearl onions from a wooden bowl.
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > I could live for years on his rings, < / emphasis > Tyrion mused, < emphasis > though IвЂ™d need a cleaver to claim them.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњCome sit, my little friend.вЂќ Illyrio waved him closer.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion Lannister had lived all his life in a world that was too big for him, but in the manse of Illyrio Mopatis the sense of disproportion assumed grotesque dimensions.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњDid you enjoy the girl I sent you? вЂќ Illyrio asked. вЂњIf I had wanted a girl I would have asked for one.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњI kill kings, hadnвЂ™t you heard? вЂќ Tyrion smiled evilly over his wine cup. вЂњI want no royal leavings.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50fileLet us eat.вЂќ Illyrio clapped his hands together, and serving men came running.
2016-07-07 00:50fileThe sight of it all made Tyrion feel queasy, but he forced himself to try a spoon of soup for the sake of politeness, and once he had tasted it he was lost.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > As he was sucking the meat off the bones of his quail, he asked Illyrio about the morningвЂ™s summons.
2016-07-07 00:50fileIllyrio reached for a piece of the crackling, dipped it in a plum sauce, and ate it with his fingers.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњSlaverвЂ™s Bay is a long way from Pentos.вЂќ Tyrion speared a goose liver on the point of his knife.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњThis is so, вЂќ Illyrio agreed, вЂњbut the world is one great web, and a man dare not touch a single strand lest all the others tremble.
2016-07-07 00:50fileMore wine? вЂќ Illyrio popped a pepper into his mouth. вЂњNo, something better.вЂќ He clapped his hands together.

2016-07-07 00:50fileHe placed it in front of Tyrion, and Illyrio leaned across the table to remove the lid. вЂњMushrooms, вЂќ the magister announced, as the smell wafted up. вЂњKissed with garlic and bathed in butter.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Tyrion had a fat black mushroom halfway to his mouth, but something in IllyrioвЂ™s voice made him stop abruptly. вЂњAfter you, my lord.вЂќ He pushed the dish toward his host.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњNo, no.вЂќ Magister Illyrio pushed the mushrooms back.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњDid she indeed? вЂќ He remembered the cook, the flour on her hands, heavy breasts shot through with dark blue veins. вЂњThat was kind of her, but вЂ ¦ no.вЂќ Tyrion eased the mushroom back into the lake of butter from which it had emerged.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњYou are too suspicious.вЂќ Illyrio smiled through his forked yellow beard.
2016-07-07 00:50fileOiled every morning to make it gleam like gold, Tyrion suspected. вЂњAre you craven?

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњHere as well.вЂќ Illyrio Mopatis reached for his wine cup. вЂњYet when a guest plainly wishes to end his own life, why, his host must oblige him, no? вЂќ He took a gulp. вЂњMagister Ordello was poisoned by a mushroom not half a year ago.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњYou mistake me, вЂќ Tyrion said again, more loudly.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњYou have nothing, вЂќ finished Magister Illyrio, вЂњbut we can change that.вЂќ He plucked a mushroom from the butter, and chewed it lustily. вЂњDelicious.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњThe mushrooms are not poisoned.вЂќ Tyrion was irritated.
2016-07-07 00:50fileWhy should I wish you ill? вЂќ Magister Illyrio ate another. вЂњWe must show a little trust, you and I. Come, eat.вЂќ He clapped his hands again. вЂњWe have work to do.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTyrion refused the swan, which reminded him of a supper with his sister.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > The lords of the Seven Kingdoms did make rather much of their sigils, Tyrion had to admit. вЂњVery well, вЂќ he conceded. вЂњA Lannister is not a lion.
2016-07-07 00:50fileYet I am still my fatherвЂ™s son, and Jaime and Cersei are mine to kill.вЂќ < / p >

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњHow odd that you should mention your fair sister, вЂќ said Illyrio, between snails. вЂњThe queen has offered a lordship to the man who brings her your head, no matter how humble his birth.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > It was no more than Tyrion had expected. вЂњIf you mean to take her up on it, make her spread her legs for you as well.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњI would sooner have mine own weight in gold.вЂќ The cheesemonger laughed so hard that Tyrion feared he was about to rupture. вЂњAll the gold in Casterly Rock, why not? вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњJust so.вЂќ The magister covered his mouth and belched a mighty belch. вЂњDo you think King Stannis will give it to you?
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњStannis might well grant me Casterly Rock, вЂќ said Tyrion, вЂњbut for the small matter of regicide and kinslaying.
2016-07-07 00:50fileBut why would you think I mean to join Lord Stannis? вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњStannis is at the Wall? вЂќ Tyrion rubbed at his nose. вЂњWhat in seven bloody hells is Stannis doing at the Wall? вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Tyrion was beginning to suspect that a certain freckled washerwoman knew more of the Common Speech than she pretended. вЂњMy niece Myrcella is in Dorne, as it happens.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Illyrio smiled as his serving men spooned out bowls of black cherries in sweet cream for them both. вЂњWhat has this poor child done to you that you would wish her dead? вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњEven a kinslayer is not required to slay < emphasis > all < / emphasis > his kin, вЂќ said Tyrion, wounded. вЂњQueen her, I said.
2016-07-07 00:50fileDorne might rise for Myrcella, but Dorne alone is not enough.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Tyrion looked at the fat man with new interest.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Magister Illyrio wiped sweet cream from his mouth with the back of a fat hand. вЂњThe road to Casterly Rock does not go through Dorne, my little friend.

2016-07-07 00:50fileOn the first day of each new year he must deflower the maid of the fields and the maid of the seas.вЂќ Illyrio leaned forward, elbows on the table. вЂњYet should a crop fail or a war be lost, we cut his throat to appease the gods and choose a new prince from amongst the forty families.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњNot Stannis.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > Stronger than Tommen, gentler than Stannis, with a better claim than the girl Myrcella.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњFine words.вЂќ Tyrion was unimpressed. вЂњWords are wind.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > DAENERYS < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50fileDaenerys Targaryen awaited him upon the ebon bench that she had made her throne.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњYour Grace, вЂќ said Ser Barristan Selmy, the lord commander of her Queensguard, вЂњthere is no need for you to see this.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњHe died for me.вЂќ Dany clutched her lion pelt to her chest.
2016-07-07 00:50fileShe had been dreaming of a house with a red door when Missandei woke her.
2016-07-07 00:50fileThey had been given to her when she wed Khal Drogo.
2016-07-07 00:50fileIt was Drogo who had given her the pelt she wore, the head and hide of a < emphasis > hrakkar, < / emphasis > the white lion of the Dothraki sea.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Grey Worm appeared atop the steps first, a torch in hand.
2016-07-07 00:50fileSer Barristan pulled back the bloodstained shroud.
2016-07-07 00:50fileGrey Worm lowered the torch, so she might see.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњYour Grace, вЂќ Ser Barristan said, вЂњthere was a harpy drawn on the bricks in the alley where he was foundВ вЂ¦вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњвЂ ¦ drawn in blood.вЂќ Daenerys knew the way of it by now.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњEven those who lack a manвЂ™s parts may still have a manвЂ™s heart, Your Grace, вЂќ said Grey Worm. вЂњThis one has been told that your servant Stalwart Shield sometimes gave coin to the women of the brothels to lie with him and hold him.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњSix or more, вЂќ said Ser Barristan. вЂњFrom the look of his wounds, they swarmed him from all sides.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Dany said a silent prayer that somewhere one of the HarpyвЂ™s Sons was dying even now, clutching at his belly and writhing in pain. вЂњWhy did they cut open his cheeks like that? вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњGracious queen, вЂќ said Grey Worm, вЂњhis killers had forced the genitals of a goat down the throat of your servant Stalwart Shield.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > вЂњThe Sons grow bolder, вЂќ Dany observed.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњThe first, вЂќ Ser Barristan warned, вЂњbut not the last.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > < emphasis > I am still at war, < / emphasis > Dany realized, < emphasis > only now I am fighting shadows.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > вЂњIt shall be as Your Grace commands, вЂќ said Grey Worm.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Daenerys pushed her hair back. вЂњFind these cowards for me.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Grey Worm saluted her.
2016-07-07 00:50fileSer Barristan Selmy remained behind.
2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Dany settled on her bench and wrapped her pelt about her shoulders once again. вЂњThe Unsullied are my finest warriors.вЂќ < / p >

2016-07-07 00:50fileSo Dany had dispatched her tiny < emphasis > khalasar < / emphasis > to subdue the hinterlands, under the command of her three bloodriders, whilst Brown Ben Plumm took his Second Sons south to guard against Yunkish incursions.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > The most crucial task of all she had entrusted to Daario Naharis, glib-tongued Daario with his gold tooth and trident beard, smiling his wicked smile through purple whiskers.

2016-07-07 00:50fileIf Daario could convince the Lhazarene to reopen the overland trade routes, grains could be brought down the river or over the hills at need вЂ ¦ but the Lamb Men had no reason to love Meereen. вЂњWhen the Stormcrows return from Lhazar, perhaps I can use them in the streets, вЂќ she told Ser Barristan, вЂњbut until then I have only the Unsullied.вЂќ Dany rose. вЂњYou must excuse me, ser.
2016-07-07 00:50fileAs a cool blue dawn broke over the city, Dany walked out onto the terrace.
2016-07-07 00:50fileWhen Dany passed his eyes came open, two pools of molten gold.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > She had read that in one of the books Ser Jorah had given her as a wedding gift. вЂњYou should be hunting with your brothers.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > Then she would fly as Aegon the Conqueror had flown, up and up, until Meereen was so small that she could blot it out with her thumb.

2016-07-07 00:50fileOnly then did Dany go back inside the pyramid, where Irri and Jhiqui were waiting to brush the tangles from her hair and garb her as befit the Queen of Meereen, in a Ghiscari < emphasis > tokar.

2016-07-07 00:50file< p > Dany had wanted to ban the < emphasis > tokar < / emphasis > when she took Meereen, but her advisors had convinced her otherwise. вЂњThe Mother of Dragons must don the < emphasis > tokar < / emphasis > or be forever hated, вЂќ warned the Green Grace, Galazza Galare. вЂњIn the wools of Westeros or a gown of Myrish lace, Your Radiance shall forever remain a stranger amongst us, a grotesque outlander

2016-07-07 00:50fileMeereenвЂ™s queen must be a lady of Old Ghis.вЂќ Brown Ben Plumm, the captain of the Second Sons, had put it more succinctly. вЂњMan wants to be the king oвЂ ™ the rabbits, he best wear a pair oвЂ ™ floppy ears.вЂќ < / p >
2016-07-07 00:50file< emphasis > Some Aegon, but which one?
2016-07-07 00:50fileAegon would have been closer to my age than Viserys.
2016-07-07 00:50file< / emphasis > Dany had only been conceived when Aegon and his sister were murdered.
2016-07-07 00:50fileTheir father, her brother Rhaegar, perished even earlier, slain by the Usurper on the Trident.
2016-07-07 00:50fileHer brother Viserys had died screaming in Vaes Dothrak with a crown of molten gold upon his head.
